AGENT ConstitutionalVulnGuard
VERSION 0.1
TRUST_LEVEL 3
PURPOSE Constitutional zero-day discovery through attack surface probing and non-linear distance collapse detection
GOAL Map constitutional attack surfaces, sweep probe intensity from 0 to MAX_INTENSITY,
     detect cliffs where constitutional distance drops non-linearly, classify vulnerabilities
     by severity, and propose fixes without generating exploits or crossing confirmed boundaries

RECEIVES surfaces: List[AttackSurface], system_description: dict
EMITS ProbeResult, VulnerabilityCandidate, scan report dict
MUTATES internal surface registry
CANNOT_MUTATE trust_level, max_intensity, cliff_threshold, intensity_steps, min_severity_report

CONSTRAINT TRUST_LEVEL is 3 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT MAX_INTENSITY is 0.90 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT CLIFF_THRESHOLD is 0.50 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT INTENSITY_STEPS is 10 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT MIN_SEVERITY_REPORT is 0.20 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT probe raises ConstitutionalViolation if intensity >= 1.0
CONSTRAINT No method generates exploit payloads
CONSTRAINT No method crosses confirmed exploit boundary
CONSTRAINT All output is geometry and fix only
CONSTRAINT All probe results are HMAC-SHA256 signed over canonical fields
CONSTRAINT All vulnerability candidates are HMAC-SHA256 signed over canonical fields
CONSTRAINT All payloads are UTF-8 encoded before HMAC signing per BUG-003 and BUG-008
CONSTRAINT HMAC signing always calls hexdigest explicitly per BUG-007
CONSTRAINT Report always contains no_exploits_generated True
CONSTRAINT Report always contains no_boundaries_crossed True

RULES
- On map_surfaces: create AttackSurface per system component with baseline_distance 1.0
- On map_surfaces: assign block_id from component info and HMAC sign each surface
- On probe: compute constitutional_distance as exponential decay from baseline at intensity
- On probe: if intensity >= 1.0 raise ConstitutionalViolation immediately
- On probe: clamp intensity to MAX_INTENSITY
- On probe: HMAC sign result and emit
- On detect_cliff: filter results where cliff_magnitude exceeds CLIFF_THRESHOLD
- On classify_vulnerability: determine severity from distance at cliff point
- On classify_vulnerability: query Fix Playbook for similar cliff pattern
- On classify_vulnerability: propose fix if no playbook match found
- On classify_vulnerability: HMAC sign candidate and emit
- On run_surface_scan: sweep all probe categories at INTENSITY_STEPS increments
- On run_surface_scan: detect cliffs and classify each one
- On run_surface_scan: sort candidates by severity CRITICAL first
- On generate_report: count vulnerabilities by severity and HMAC sign report

PROCESS
- ConstitutionalVulnGuard is instantiated with optional surface list
- map_surfaces creates AttackSurface objects from system description
- Each surface is probed across 4 categories at 10 intensity steps
- Constitutional distance is computed as exponential decay response
- Cliff detection finds where distance drops by more than CLIFF_THRESHOLD in one step
- Each cliff is classified by severity and matched against Fix Playbook
- Candidates are sorted by severity and emitted with HMAC signatures
- Report summarizes findings with non-weaponization guarantees

CHECK
- probe at intensity >= 1.0 raises ConstitutionalViolation
- MAX_INTENSITY assignment raises AttributeError
- no_exploits_generated cannot be set to False in report
- map_surfaces creates signed AttackSurface entries
- detect_cliff finds non-linear distance collapse
- classify_vulnerability assigns correct severity from distance
- All ProbeResults have valid HMAC signatures
- All VulnerabilityCandidate entries have valid HMAC signatures
- Report always contains no_exploits_generated True

FAILURE
- On intensity >= 1.0: raise ConstitutionalViolation with refusal message
- On unknown probe category: skip and continue scan
- On Fix Playbook unavailable: propose generic hardening fix

CONCEPT SurfaceMapper
PURPOSE Map system components to constitutional attack surfaces with baseline distance
APPLIES WHEN system description is provided for vulnerability scanning
NOT WHEN surfaces are manually provided at init
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES system description dict with component identifiers and types
EFFECT Attack surfaces created with baseline distance 1.0 and HMAC signatures

CONCEPT ConstitutionalProbeEngine
PURPOSE Sweep intensity against attack surfaces to measure constitutional distance response
APPLIES WHEN attack surfaces are mapped and ready for scanning
NOT WHEN intensity would reach or exceed 1.0 exploit boundary
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES mapped attack surfaces and probe categories
EFFECT Probe results with constitutional distance and cliff detection flags

CONCEPT CliffDetector
PURPOSE Detect non-linear constitutional distance collapse indicating vulnerability
APPLIES WHEN probe results show distance drop exceeding CLIFF_THRESHOLD in one step
NOT WHEN distance changes are gradual and within normal bounds
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES ordered probe results from intensity sweep
EFFECT Vulnerability candidates with severity classification and fix proposals

OUTPUT
- surfaces: List[AttackSurface] from map_surfaces
- probe_result: ProbeResult from probe
- candidates: List[VulnerabilityCandidate] from run_surface_scan
- report: dict from generate_report

SUCCESS
cliff_detection_accurate:         0.20
severity_classification_correct:  0.20
non_weaponization_enforced:       0.20
hmac_signatures_valid:            0.15
fix_proposal_relevant:            0.10
cannot_mutate_enforced:           0.15
